3.8. Add "Lumber Delivery / Pickup Date" Date Field & Behavior

  


Requirements

Sometimes the Lumber package is delivered/picked up at a separate date than the truss package. Triple D would like to add a separate field for this date. 

  * Rename the underlying field names for "Delivery / Pickup Date" and "Delivery / Pickup Time" to show that they are "General" but leave displayed names on the detail screen and printouts as they currently are. 
  * Add "Lumber Delivery / Pickup Date" field above the "Lumber Delivery" checkboxes column heading. 
    * This should only be visible for quotes/orders with both Lumber and at least one other package (if the order has only Lumber, it will simply use the General Date)  
    * This should have an underlying field name to show that it is Lumber-specific
    * Require a date in this field before changing the the order status to Order (allow it to be blank when in Quote status)
    * This is primarily a reference field (inventory is still adjusted based on the General Date) 
  * When saving, blank out any hidden dates (Lumber). 
  * If the user enters a date in General Delivery / Pickup Date field, it should auto-fill into the Lumber Delivery / Pickup Date field. Changes to the General Date field will not update the Lumber Date. 
  * If there is Lumber and at least one other package in the order, the Lumber package should be considered complete (and should be locked) when the Lumber Date is in the past. 
  * The whole Order should be marked complete and locked when the order passes the General Date (even if the General Date is before the Lumber Date. 
  * Adjust the message at the top of the detail screen (there should now be two messages that display conditionally): 
    * One message when only the Lumber date is past: 
      * "This order has passed the Delivery / Pickup Date for the Lumber package, which therefore is considered complete." 
    * Another message when the General date/both dates are past: 
      * "This whole order has passed the Delivery / Pickup Date and therefore is considered complete."
  * It is not necessary to have a Lumber Delivery / Pickup time. 
  * It is not necessary to have a separate Metal Delivery / Pickup date or time. 
  * On the Quote/Order printouts and the Packing List printout: 
    * Add a new row for "Lumber Delivery / Pickup Date" below the current Delivery / Pickup Date and Time row. 
    * This should show conditionally (depending on whether the Lumber Date is showing in the order) 
    * If one of the dates is blank, the entire row on the printout should be blank.
    * See example of the Quote/Order Printout:

Time Estimate: 2.5 days
